## Project Overview

As part of the Global People Operations team, I supported the validation of an HR Headcount Dashboard used for workforce reporting. My responsibility was to verify that the dashboard accurately reflected employee data available in Oracle EBS before it was used for business reporting.

Rather than developing the dashboard, I focused on validating the accuracy of the reported data by comparing dashboard metrics with source reports extracted from Oracle EBS.

## Business Objective

The objective of this project was to ensure that the HR dashboard displayed accurate workforce information by validating dashboard data against the source records available in Oracle EBS.

The validation process helped maintain confidence in business reports used by HR and management teams.

## My Role

My responsibilities included:

- Downloading source reports from Oracle EBS.
- Comparing dashboard data with Oracle EBS reports.
- Validating employee headcount and workforce metrics.
- Verifying that dashboard information accurately reflected the source data.
- Supporting regular validation activities as dashboard data was refreshed periodically.

## Dashboard Metrics Validated

The dashboard included workforce information such as:

- Total Headcount
- Joiners
- Leavers
- Internal Joinees
- Country-wise Headcount
- Department-wise Headcount
- Gender-wise Headcount


## Validation Process

The dashboard validation followed a structured process:

1. Download the latest workforce reports from Oracle EBS.
2. Review the dashboard after its scheduled data refresh.
3. Compare dashboard values with Oracle EBS source reports.
4. Verify employee counts across different reporting categories.
5. Confirm that the dashboard accurately reflected the source data before business reporting.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Oracle EBS] --> B[Source Report Download]
    B --> C[Dashboard Refresh]
    C --> D[Data Comparison]
    D --> E[Headcount Validation]
    E --> F[Business Reporting]
```

## Challenges Faced

The validation process itself was well established. The primary challenge was ensuring that dashboard values consistently matched the Oracle EBS source reports after each scheduled refresh. Careful comparison of employee data across multiple reporting categories was essential to maintain reporting accuracy.

